                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/10–1644</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-16">October 16,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In regard to this Indochina matter, it is my judgment on this date that we should
                    do nothing in regard to resistance groups or in any other way in relation to
                    Indochina. You might bring it up to me a little later when things are a little
                    clearer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
